
[1]pec-cary

   PEC-CARY, n. A quadruped of Mexico, in general appearance resembling a
   hog, but its body is less bulky, its legs shorter, and its bristles
   thicker and stronger, like the quills of the porcupine. Its color is
   black and white, and it has on the hind part of the back a protuberance
   like the navel of other animals, with an orifice form which issues a
   liquor of a very strong scent.
